HEADWORD: Dotal
<hw>Do"tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>dotalis</ets>,
fr. <ets>dos</ets>, <ets>dotis</ets>, dowry: cf. F. <ets>dotal</ets>.
See <er>Dot</er> dowry.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to dower, or a woman's
marriage portion; constituting dower, or comprised in it.</def>
<rj><au>Garth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
